Hi @fainashalts,
I think I am getting error at this line:
MyContract5(address(throwproxy)).storeNum(22);

In the MyContract5 constructor is empty and in the above statement I am passing a value to it as done in the tutorial. The statement before its is:
 
ThrowProxy throwproxy = new ThrowProxy(address(mycontract));
This is storing the address of MyContract5 in 'throwproxy'. So we have to call storeNum(22) using throwproxy and I can't do that.


However, if change Assert(...) to require(...) in TestMyContract5 i.e

pragma solidity ^0.4.22;
